AGI - Piove unrest on Milan> from last night.&nbsp; The incessant rain has led to the flooding of the Lambro> river in some areas. Firefighters let us know that the flood is "controlled and monitored permanently", although of course it is causing floods and inconveniences". The Councillor for Security of the City of Milan Marco Granelli in a video on his Facebook profile, explains that the levels of the Seveso have increased > with the rains of tonight, so as to make necessary the activation of the lamination tank> of the Seveso, which protects the neighborhoods of Niguarda, Prato Centenaro and Isola. "Once again this fundamental work has come into operation to protect the city. Very high also the Lambro levels, above 2,50 meters". "We evacuated communities last night - says the Councillor - so we don't have problems." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"Let's rain again today and tomorrow. The employees of the commune and the city councillor are around tonight. The situation of the Seveso is under control, we have the Bresso tank in operation, that of Lentate will be in function of 50% by the end of the year, then will be in realization two more in Paderno and Lentate. They are large basins, but a bathtub can accommodate water to a certain level". The mayor of Milan, Giuseppe Sala, explained this in a direct social. "It is an activity that is engaging us from tonight - he added -. On the other hand, we have some problems on the Lambro where we have a bathtub planned around Monza but we are still at the project. Milan must be protected but the tanks must be realized not in Milan and therefore sometimes there are problems with the municipalities and the Lombardy Region".

